      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:2:46:7",
      "text": [
        " مُكَاتَبٍ مَاتَ وَ قَدْ أَدَّى مِنْ مُكَاتَبَتِهِ شَيْئاً وَ تَرَكَ مَالًا وَ لَهُ وِلْدَانٌ أَحْرَارٌ فَقَالَ إِنَّ عَلِيّاً ( عليه السلام ) كَانَ يَقُولُ يُجْعَلُ مَالُهُ بَيْنَهُمْ بِالْحِصَصِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Abdullah Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Al Hakam, from Aban, from Muhammad Bin Muslim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from one of the two (5<sup>th</sup> or 6<sup>th</sup> Imam<sup>asws</sup>) regarding a contracted slave who died and he had paid off something from his contracted amount, and left wealth, and for him were two free children. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Ali<sup>asws</sup> was saying: ‘Make his wealth to be between them with the quotas’."
        ]
      }
    },
